.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-2-20::.
There are 3 different nationalities: argentine, german, canadian
3 different brands of cigars are smoked: baccarat, oliveros, havana
The people have 3 different jobs:  electrician, accountant, fisherman
The people use 3 different means of transport: car, train, tram
1. the argentine is on the right of the accountant##1
2. the oliveros-smoker is the person driving the car##1
3. the accountant is the person driving the car##1
4. the electrician is the canadian##1
5. the havana-smoker is between the person driving the tram and the accountant##2
6. the fisherman is the argentine##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |      1       |     2     |     3      |
| Nationality        | german      | argentine | canadian |
| Cigar         | oliveros     | havana    | baccarat        |
| Job       | accountant | fisherman   | electrician   |
| Transport   | car          | train     | tram       |

 